data.description: Located in the desirable Sheridan Park neighborhood in a quiet  three story walk-up. This vintage 2 bedroom, 1.5 bathroom is a designers dream. A total rehab and is being sold "As-Is". The spacious living space features a wood burning fireplace with a timeless Pewabic tile mantle. Wet bar and large deck, set off the living room invites an enticing space for summer get togethers while viewing the beautiful tree lined street. A sizeable dining room located off the kitchen is perfect for entertaining and also family dining. The en-suite primary bedroom is equipped with  ample closets and a ceiling fan. The second bedroom can be utilized as a small bedroom or a great at home office space.  Additional unit highlights include hardwood and laminate floors throughout. A second outdoor deck, nicely landscaped backyard,  one outdoor parking space, and large storage space all accessed  from the kitchen. Also included is a combined washer/dryer unit.  Pet friendly building.  Conveniently located and walking distance to the train, many  restaurants, coffee houses, shopping, Target, library and post office. Minutes from Lake Shore Drive, Montrose Harbor,  Andersonville and Lincoln Square.
